<subSubSection id="02C76566B830FFC0FF1DED90B064F9FA" pageId="2" pageNumber="177" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4A6236EDB830FFC0FF1DED90B064F9FA" blockId="2.[136,1452,1475,2005]" pageId="2" pageNumber="177">Diagnosis:—The species is characterized by a stipe or pileus turning bluish when bruised, absence of an annulus or veil, a yellowish brown to bright yellow, smooth, slightly sticky, shining pileus, yellowish to dark purple-brown lamellae, hexagonal basidiospores (6.5–) 8.5–10 (–11) × (4–) 5–6 (–6.5) μm, pleurocystidia and cheilocystidia clavateventricose to fusoid-clavate, sometimes sublageniform with slightly long, sinuous neck.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
